ze:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-go&#34; data-lang=&#34;go&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;	&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;linenumber&#34;&gt;22&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-go&#34; data-lang=&#34;go&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;	&lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;// Wait for the goroutine to finish&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;linenumber&#34;&gt;23&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-go&#34; data-lang=&#34;go&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;	&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;msg&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;ch&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;linenumber&#34;&gt;24&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-go&#34; data-lang=&#34;go&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;	&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;fmt&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;Println&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;msg&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;linenumber&#34;&gt;25&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-go&#34; data-lang=&#34;go&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;linenumber&#34;&gt;26&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-go&#34; data-lang=&#34;go&#34;&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/pre&gt; 
&lt;h2 id=&#34;how-it-works&#34;&gt;How It Works&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The VSCode theme styling is achieved through CSS variables that match VS Code&amp;rsquo;s default dark theme colors. These variables define colors for different code elements like:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keywords&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Functions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Numbers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Class names&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Variables&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Properties&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operators and punctuation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The syntax highlighting is powered by Hugo&amp;rsquo;s built-in syntax highlighter, while the VSCode-like appearance is provided by our custom CSS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;conclusion&#34;&gt;Conclusion&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Using the VSCode theme for your code blocks makes your technical blog posts look more professional and improves readability. Feel free to use this in your own posts!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Remember to set &lt;code&gt;draft: false&lt;/code&gt; when you&amp;rsquo;re ready to publish this post.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
